---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import MainNavigation from '../components/MainNavigation';
import ContactSection from '../components/ContactSection';
import Footer from '../components/Footer';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Layout 
  title="Terms of Service | United Security Virginia" 
  description="Terms of service for United Security Virginia. Review our service terms, conditions, and agreements for security system installation and monitoring services."
  type="website"
>
	<MainNavigation client:load />
	
	<!-- Hero Section -->
	<section class="relative py-24 lg:py-32 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-100 via-gray-200 to-gray-300 overflow-hidden">
		<div class="relative container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
				<h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-header mb-6">
					Terms of Service
				</h1>
				<p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl text-header mb-8 leading-relaxed">
					Service agreements and terms for United Security Virginia
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Main Content -->
	<section class="py-16 bg-white">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">
				<p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-8">
					<strong>Last Updated:</strong> January 1, 2024
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-header mb-4">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-header leading-relaxed mb-6">
					By using the services of United Security Virginia ("Company," "we," "us," or "our") or accessing our website, you ("Customer," "you," or "your") agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our services.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-header mb-4">2. Services Provided</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-header leading-relaxed mb-4">
					United Security Virginia provides security services including but not limited to:
				</p>
				<ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-header mb-6">
					<li>• Security system design, installation, and maintenance</li>
					<li>• Access control systems and electronic locks</li>
					<li>• Video surveillance and monitoring systems</li>
					<li>• Commercial locksmith services</li>
					<li>• Security consulting and assessments</li>
					<li>• Emergency response and repair services</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-header mb-4">3. Service Agreements and Contracts</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-header leading-relaxed mb-4">
					All services are provided under specific service agreements that include:
				</p>
				<ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-header mb-6">
					<li>• Detailed scope of work and equipment specifications</li>
					<li>• Installation timeline and service schedules</li>
					<li>• Pricing, payment terms, and warranty information</li>
					<li>• Customer responsibilities and access requirements</li>
					<li>• Maintenance and support provisions</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-header mb-4">4. Customer Responsibilities</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-header leading-relaxed mb-4">
					As a customer, you agree to:
				</p>
				<ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-header mb-6">
					<li>• Provide accurate information about your security needs and property</li>
					<li>• Ensure safe and reasonable access to installation locations</li>
					<li>• Notify us of any changes to your property or security requirements</li>
					<li>• Use security systems in accordance with manufacturer guidelines</li>
					<li>• Maintain electrical power and internet connectivity as required</li>
					<li>• Report system issues or malfunctions promptly</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-header mb-4">5. Payment Terms</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-header leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Payment terms include:
				</p>
				<ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-header mb-6">
					<li>• Installation fees are due upon completion of work</li>
					<li>• Service fees are due according to the agreed schedule</li>
					<li>• Late payments may incur additional charges</li>
					<li>• We reserve the right to suspend services for non-payment</li>
					<li>• Returned check fees may apply for insufficient funds</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-header mb-4">6. Warranties and Guarantees</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-header leading-relaxed mb-4">
					We provide warranties as follows:
				</p>
				<ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-header mb-6">
					<li>• Installation workmanship warranty for one year</li>
					<li>• Equipment warranties per manufacturer specifications</li>
					<li>• Service guarantee for professional installation and support</li>
					<li>• Warranty claims must be reported within the warranty period</li>
					<li>• Warranties do not cover damage from misuse or external factors</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-header mb-4">7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-header leading-relaxed mb-6">
					While we strive to provide reliable security services, our liability is limited to the amount paid for services. We are not liable for losses due to equipment failure, power outages, internet disruptions, or other factors beyond our control. Security systems are designed to reduce risk but cannot guarantee prevention of all security incidents.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-header mb-4">8. Emergency Services</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-header leading-relaxed mb-6">
					For emergency services, we will make reasonable efforts to respond promptly. However, response times may vary based on weather, traffic, technician availability, and other factors. Emergency service fees may apply for after-hours calls.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-header mb-4">9. Intellectual Property</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-header leading-relaxed mb-6">
					Our system designs, configurations, and technical documentation remain our intellectual property. Customers receive a license to use installed systems but may not reproduce or distribute our proprietary designs or software.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-header mb-4">10. Privacy and Confidentiality</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-header leading-relaxed mb-6">
					We respect your privacy and maintain confidentiality of your security arrangements. Our privacy practices are detailed in our Privacy Policy. We may access your property for installation, maintenance, and service purposes as authorized.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-header mb-4">11. Service Termination</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-header leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Either party may terminate services with appropriate notice:
				</p>
				<ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-header mb-6">
					<li>• Customer may cancel services with 30 days written notice</li>
					<li>• We may terminate services for non-payment or breach of terms</li>
					<li>• Equipment ownership depends on service agreement terms</li>
					<li>• Final payment is due upon service termination</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-header mb-4">12. Virginia State Law</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-header leading-relaxed mb-6">
					These terms are governed by Virginia state law. We are licensed by the Virginia Department of Criminal Justice Services (DCJS# 11-3283) and comply with all applicable Virginia regulations for private security services.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-header mb-4">13. Dispute Resolution</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-header leading-relaxed mb-6">
					Any disputes will first be addressed through direct communication. If resolution cannot be reached, disputes may be submitted to mediation or arbitration as specified in individual service agreements.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-header mb-4">14. Modifications to Terms</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-header leading-relaxed mb-6">
					We reserve the right to modify these terms with reasonable notice. Continued use of our services after changes constitutes acceptance of modified terms. Significant changes will be communicated directly to customers.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-header mb-4">15. Contact Information</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-header leading-relaxed mb-4">
					For questions about these terms or our services, contact us:
				</p>
				<div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
					<p class="text-lg text-header mb-2"><strong>United Security Virginia</strong></p>
					<p class="text-lg text-header mb-2">Phone: <a href="tel:540-989-9393" class="text-primary hover:underline">540-989-9393</a></p>
					<p class="text-lg text-header mb-2">Email: info@unitedsecurityva.com</p>
					<p class="text-lg text-header mb-2">License: DCJS# 11-3283</p>
					<p class="text-lg text-header">Service Area: Southwest Virginia</p>
				</div>

				<div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 p-6 rounded-lg mt-8">
					<p class="text-lg text-header">
						<strong>Professional Service Commitment:</strong> United Security Virginia has been serving Southwest Virginia since 1988 with professional, licensed security services. We are committed to providing quality installations, reliable service, and customer satisfaction.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<ContactSection client:load />
	<Footer client:load />
</Layout>